<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-4073] MirrorMaker should handle mirroring messages w/o timestamp better</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4073</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, if the 0.10.0.1 MirrorMaker reads a message w/o timestamp from the source cluster, it will hit the following exception. This was introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3787&quot; title=&quot;Preserve message timestamp in mirror mkaer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-3787&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-3787&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. So it only affects 0.10.0.1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;16/08/2016:18:26:41 PDT&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;FATAL&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;kafka.tools.MirrorMaker$MirrorMakerThread mirrormaker-thread-1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;mirrormaker-thread-1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Mirror maker thread failure due to&lt;br/&gt;
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Invalid timestamp -1&lt;br/&gt;
at org.apache.kafka.clients.producer.ProducerRecord.&amp;lt;init&amp;gt;(ProducerRecord.java:60)&lt;br/&gt;
at kafka.tools.MirrorMaker$defaultMirrorMakerMessageHandler$.handle(MirrorMaker.scala:678)&lt;br/&gt;
at kafka.tools.MirrorMaker$MirrorMakerThread.run(MirrorMaker.scala:414)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
